  "description": "Operational requirements and constraints for running Connect on Swarm: full Bee v2.7+ nodes, mutable depth-22+ stamps, wallet, open P2P ports.",
  "orientation": "Connect-on-Swarm has a hard floor of operational requirements: Bee v2.7.1+ full nodes (light nodes can't receive PSS or GSOC), mutable depth-22+ postage stamps, an Ethereum wallet, and open P2P ports. Within that, feed-backing stamps must be mutable to avoid bucket exhaustion, GSOC subscriptions only work on full nodes, and Bee v2.7.0 auto-races legacy vs. wrapped feed versions so adapter code no longer picks a version. This MOC is the pragmatic deployment reference for anyone onboarding a Bee node for Connect.",
